Proposed (18.9s): Use this skill when a controlled-vocabulary CSV (termbase.csv, glossary csv, approved/preferred terms list — often the output of a terminology audit) already exists and the user wants to put it to work downstream: (1) render it into agent or reviewer context — an AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md vocabulary section or a compact preamble block for a spec/proposal — so writers and codegen agents stop inventing synonyms; (2) check or lint a draft spec, proposal, or tasks file against the approved terms and report wording drift, banned variants, or flip-flopping between synonyms; (3) after an implementation or refactor, find recurring new domain terms not yet in the termbase and report candidates with counts and locations (read-only; never edits the termbase). Trigger for any request to enforce, apply, or make specs/agents "actually follow" an existing term list. Do NOT use to create a termbase or audit docs to build a glossary from scratch — that's terminology-audit; this skill consumes the finished CSV.

